Jester rats

Jester Rats:

Jester Rats are a common presence within the Bilefair, small rat-like creatures known for their uncanny mimicry and unsettling behaviour.

Appearance:

These creatures are easily identified by their:

  • Tiny, makeshift jester hats adorned with jingling bells
  • Jerky, almost puppet-like movements
  • Loud, high-pitched imitations of laughter

Social behaviour:

They often gather in small groups, performing eerily accurate renditions of:

  • Jester performances
  • Slapstick routines
  • Mock tumbling or juggling acts

These mimicries appear to be a form of social or survival behaviour, as they perform for:

  • Food scraps
  • Drugs dropped by passers-by
  • The attention of larger, more dangerous creatures

Despite their comical appearance, their behaviour is tinged with a desperate edge, suggesting mimicry born from fear or instinct rather than joy.

Additional:

Due to their small size, and proximity to the ground, within the Bilefair realm, these creatures are often intoxicated via the drugs in the Slick clouds of the realm
